1
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:16,080
Earth is gone.
地球消失了

2
00:01:18,587 --> 00:01:21,043
Earth never existed!
地球从没存在过！

3
00:01:23,801 --> 00:01:25,509
Halt, Michael!
停下来，迈克尔！

4
00:01:25,636 --> 00:01:29,385
Do you hear me! We will save you!
能听得到吗？我们想要救你！

5
00:02:35,424 --> 00:02:38,591
Do you hear me, Michael?
能听到吗？迈克尔！

6
00:02:39,887 --> 00:02:43,007
Michael! Stop!
迈克尔！停下来！

7
00:02:45,435 --> 00:02:48,009
Pull yourself together, Michael!
振作起来，迈克尔！

8
00:03:55,139 --> 00:03:57,179
I'm going with you.
我和你一起去
- Better not.
最好不要

9
00:03:57,308 --> 00:03:59,431
For the two us, it would be...You'd only hold me back.
这是我俩的事...你只要确保我能回来

10
00:03:59,561 --> 00:04:02,645
It's the only way to save him.
这是救他的唯一办法

11
00:04:03,315 --> 00:04:05,984
And maybe even us.
或许也是救我们的

12
00:04:06,485 --> 00:04:08,608
I'll be back in an hour.
一个小时后我会回来

13
00:04:12,575 --> 00:04:14,402
What is he doing?
他在干嘛？

14
00:04:17,289 --> 00:04:19,116
Michael!
迈克尔！

15
00:04:19,875 --> 00:04:24,253
Michael! Do you hear me? We'll save you!
迈克尔！能听见吗？我们来救你了！

16
00:04:24,714 --> 00:04:27,834
Do you hear me, Michael?
能听见吗，迈克尔！

17
00:04:29,011 --> 00:04:31,050
There's no other signal.
没有其他信号

18
00:04:32,973 --> 00:04:35,215
We will wait then.
那我们就等着吧

19
00:04:52,871 --> 00:04:56,536
We have travelled billions of kilometres.
我们已经航行了数十亿公里

20
00:04:57,584 --> 00:05:01,084
We are almost at the end of our journey.
快到了旅程的终点

21
00:05:02,006 --> 00:05:07,132
Time will pass and children will learn that we were the first
时间总会过去，孩子们会学到我们是

22
00:05:07,387 --> 00:05:11,338
who had set out on a journey
through the Universe to find life
第一批穿越宇宙前往半人马座阿尔法星

23
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:14,685
on the planets of Alpha Centauri.
寻找生命的人

24
00:05:30,080 --> 00:05:34,327
Geneva. Based on the latest news from
the World Aeronautics and Space Centre
日内瓦，根据世界航空航天中心最新消息

25
00:05:34,543 --> 00:05:38,126
the Ikaria launch maneuvres are running according to schedule.
伊卡利号发射演习正在按计划进行

26
00:05:38,381 --> 00:05:42,924
After 8 years of preparations, Ikaria
ceases to be one of Earth's satellites.
经过8年的准备，伊卡利号不再是地球的卫星

27
00:05:43,261 --> 00:05:48,802
Ikaria XB 1 in fact is a small space town for forty inhabitants.
伊卡利号实际上是一个小型太空城，可容纳40位居民

28
00:05:49,435 --> 00:05:52,222
Alpha Centauri was chosen as the destination of the mission
半人马座阿尔法星，被选作这次任务的目的地

29
00:05:52,355 --> 00:05:55,226
not only for being a star closest to Earth.
不仅仅是因为它是距离地球最近的恒星

30
00:05:55,358 --> 00:05:59,403
The decisive factor was that it is
similar to our Sun and has several
决定性的因素是它与我们的太阳相似

31
00:05:59,655 --> 00:06:02,989
planets orbiting it, where the existence of life is anticipated.
并且有几个行星环绕，预计那里会有生命存在

32
00:06:25,434 --> 00:06:28,471
Throughout its construction Ikaria orbited Earth
遍及它的构造，伊卡利号就像

33
00:06:28,604 --> 00:06:31,060
as a stationary satellite.
一个同步卫星绕着地球运行

34
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:37,146
What will your father be doing on the Ikaria?
你父亲将在伊卡利号上做什么？
- Nothing.
什么也不做

35
00:06:37,739 --> 00:06:39,779
How come nothing?
怎么什么也不不做？
- Nothing.
什么也不做

36
00:06:39,909 --> 00:06:42,115
When they land on some planet,
当他们在某个星球着陆

37
00:06:42,245 --> 00:06:45,448
he will collect flowers and animals.
他会采集一些花啦动物啦一类的

38
00:06:46,499 --> 00:06:49,417
As we all know, Ikaria will return in 15 years.
众所周知，伊卡利号将在15年后返回

39
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:53,336
Due to time dilatation, however, its crew, to put it popularly,
由于时间膨胀效应，它的船员，通俗点说

40
00:06:53,549 --> 00:06:56,883
will only be 28 months older.
他们的年龄只会增长28个月

41
00:06:57,262 --> 00:07:04,012
Mars. Our reporter informs us that
Ikaria has crossed Jupiter's orbit.
火星，我们的记者向我们报告，
伊卡利号已经穿过木星轨道

42
00:07:04,269 --> 00:07:07,769
It should leave the solar system today.
今天就会离开太阳系

43
00:07:20,371 --> 00:07:22,993
Master Computer.
主机

44
00:07:23,249 --> 00:07:26,167
End of increased G-force.
增加重力结束

45
00:07:27,087 --> 00:07:29,163
Normal regime.
正常生活规律

46
00:07:30,758 --> 00:07:33,000
Autoregulation off.
自动调节取消

47
00:07:37,891 --> 00:07:40,643
That's that.
就是这样

48
00:07:41,395 --> 00:07:43,435
Get up, girls.
姑娘们，起来了

49
00:07:48,194 --> 00:07:51,646
How are you feeling, Stephie?
感觉怎样，思戴菲

50
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:54,910
She was frightened.
她受惊了吧
- And you? - Me?
-你呢？-我？

51
00:07:55,077 --> 00:07:57,485
Just don't pretend to be a hero!
被逞英雄了！

52
00:07:57,955 --> 00:08:00,197
Especially not in front of your wife.
尤其是在你妻子面前

53
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,873
The lift off is not easy for anyone.
起飞对任何人都不容易

54
00:08:03,044 --> 00:08:05,915
I thought it would be worse.
我原以为会更糟

55
00:08:07,549 --> 00:08:10,219
Commander MacDonald to the transmission room.
麦克唐纳指挥官请到发射室

56
00:08:17,853 --> 00:08:20,309
If you only knew how many things I wanted to tell you.
你要是知道我有多少话想对你说就好了

57
00:08:20,439 --> 00:08:22,266
I know.
我知道

58
00:08:23,275 --> 00:08:25,482
And I'm just saying a lot of nonsense now.
我现在说的都是废话

59
00:08:25,611 --> 00:08:26,987
What have you got there?
你在那得到了什么？

60
00:08:27,113 --> 00:08:30,364
I picked it up in our garden. A pebble.
是在花园里捡到的，一个鹅卵石

61
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,705
Why...
为什么...

62
00:08:38,793 --> 00:08:41,878
Why are you looking at me like that?
为什么你用那样的眼神看着我？

63
00:08:43,131 --> 00:08:46,133
When you come back...
当你回来的时候
- I know.
我知道

64
00:08:47,094 --> 00:08:49,051
You'll be older than me.
你会比我老

65
00:08:49,180 --> 00:08:52,383
I won't like you.
我不会喜欢你的
- It's not funny.
这不好笑

66
00:08:53,351 --> 00:08:55,391
You'll look the same.
你会跟现在一样美

67
00:08:56,146 --> 00:08:58,816
I'll have a fifteen year old daughter.
我将有一个15岁的女儿

68
00:08:59,692 --> 00:09:02,148
What? Rena! Rena!
什么？瑞纳！瑞纳！

69
00:09:02,278 --> 00:09:05,694
Navigation room! What's the matter?
导航室！怎么了？

70
00:09:08,034 --> 00:09:11,902
We're losing communication with Earth, hurry up.
我们跟地球联系不上了，快！

71
00:09:15,126 --> 00:09:18,827
I was afraid we wouldn't even say goodbye.
恐怕来不及说再见了

72
00:09:21,341 --> 00:09:23,749
This time, there will be two us waiting for you.
此时此刻，我们两个在等你回来

73
00:09:23,886 --> 00:09:26,377
I was so anxious to teach her first steps.
恐怕我不能教她走路了

74
00:09:26,555 --> 00:09:28,928
Now, I will see her for the first time when she's 15.
当她15岁时，我才能第一次见她

75
00:09:29,058 --> 00:09:31,016
You can teach her to dance.
你可以教她跳舞啊

76
00:09:31,144 --> 00:09:33,516
She wouldn't thank me for that.
她并不会因此感谢我的

77
00:09:33,647 --> 00:09:35,556
How are you feeling?
你感觉怎样？

78
00:09:35,691 --> 00:09:38,894
Are you happy that you're finally flying?
终于能飞向太空了，开心吗？

79
00:09:40,571 --> 00:09:43,027
It's a pity you can't fly with us.
遗憾的是你无法跟我们一起

80
00:09:44,868 --> 00:09:46,695
What's the matter?
怎么了？

81
00:09:48,038 --> 00:09:50,790
Never mind. Give my regards to Stephie.
没事，代我向思戴菲问好

82
00:09:52,752 --> 00:09:55,623
Tell her that...
跟她说...

83
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:59,878
I wish her a bon voyage.
祝她旅途愉快

84
00:10:00,052 --> 00:10:02,590
To Stephie?
是思戴菲？
- Don't forget it.
别忘了

85
00:10:05,099 --> 00:10:06,510
Rena...
瑞纳...

86
00:10:11,356 --> 00:10:12,767
Rena.
瑞纳...

87
00:10:15,402 --> 00:10:20,742
He wanted to confuse the computer.
He ordered smoked bananas.
他是不是想想玩坏电脑啊，竟命令它去熏香蕉

88
00:10:21,075 --> 00:10:23,152
Dried beefbroth.
脱水牛肉汤
- And steak with what?
还有牛排加什么？

89
00:10:23,286 --> 00:10:24,484
With honey.
加蜂蜜
- With honey.
加蜂蜜

90
00:10:24,788 --> 00:10:27,458
And ice cream on garlic.
大蒜冰激凌
- And a steak with honey.
还有牛排蘸蜂蜜

91
00:10:28,584 --> 00:10:30,162
And this came out.
然后这玩意就弄出来了

92
00:10:30,461 --> 00:10:31,576
Enjoy it!
好好享受这美味吧！

93
00:10:31,879 --> 00:10:34,881
This is how our ancestors imagined space food.
这就是古人幻想的太空食物

94
00:10:35,175 --> 00:10:36,550
Romantics.
浪漫啊

95
00:10:43,267 --> 00:10:45,937
Well, I've finished my lunch.
好吧，我已经吃完了

96
00:10:47,814 --> 00:10:49,558
Anthony.
安东尼

97
00:10:49,941 --> 00:10:51,851
Bon appetit.
愿你胃口好

98
00:10:52,402 --> 00:11:00,067
It's June 26, 2163.
今天是2163年6月26日

99
00:11:00,203 --> 00:11:05,827
Morning temperatures around 15 degrees.
早上温度15度
- This is the miracle of the last century.
这玩意是上个世纪的奇迹

100
00:11:06,085 --> 00:11:09,454
A man of metal that not only...
金属人并不是仅仅...
- Wait, don't touch him.
等一下，别碰他

101
00:11:09,964 --> 00:11:12,087
Cloudy, cloudy, cloudy...
多云，多云，多云...

102
00:11:15,136 --> 00:11:17,295
Did you take it with you again?
你又把它带走了吗?

103
00:11:17,431 --> 00:11:21,511
As much as I remember, all crew members may take with them:
就我所记得的，所有船员都可以带上他们

104
00:11:21,644 --> 00:11:25,013
Firstly, as many personal items, as they wish.
首先，如他们所愿，同人类一样多的材料

105
00:11:25,148 --> 00:11:27,686
Secondly...
其次...
- This is a personal item?
这是一个私人的物品?

106
00:11:27,943 --> 00:11:29,686
I have him for eighty years.
我拥有他已经八十年了

107
00:11:29,903 --> 00:11:31,695
It's quite ancient then.
那可真是太古老了

108
00:11:32,197 --> 00:11:33,396
What?
什么？

109
00:11:33,616 --> 00:11:35,692
But what will you do with it here, Anthony?
但在这儿，安东尼，你将怎么处置它呢？

110
00:11:35,827 --> 00:11:39,113
What do you mean? He always flies with me.
你什么意思？他总是伴随着我飞行

111
00:11:40,373 --> 00:11:44,585
But all the robots here are controlled
centrally and are specialised.
但这里所有的机器人都被集中控制并且是专业化的

112
00:11:44,878 --> 00:11:50,040
Why should I care! Patrick is universal. He can do anything.
这关我什么事！帕特里克是全能的，他能干任何事情

113
00:11:50,885 --> 00:11:52,712
But it's good for nothing.
但是它毫无用处

114
00:11:55,057 --> 00:11:58,141
Let's go Patrick.
咱们走，帕特里克
- Let's go.
咱们走

115
00:12:01,731 --> 00:12:04,518
Not there.
不是那儿
- Not there.
不是那儿

116
00:12:18,792 --> 00:12:22,126
Who is she?
她是谁？
- The new officer.
新船员

117
00:12:22,504 --> 00:12:25,043
What new officer? I don't know about any new officer.
什么新船员？我不认识任何新船员

118
00:12:25,174 --> 00:12:29,587
She's flying instead of MacDonald's
wife. A historian. Why?
她是来替麦克唐纳的妻子的，是个历史学家，怎么了？

119
00:12:29,721 --> 00:12:31,263
Never mind.
没事

120
00:12:31,556 --> 00:12:33,181
I don't know.
我不知道

121
00:12:33,559 --> 00:12:36,132
Don't tell me that it's not possible.
别跟我讲不可能
- It is, but on Earth.
可能，不过是在地球上

122
00:12:36,312 --> 00:12:40,061
Come on, Peter. A dandelion or a daisy would do, or...
过来，彼得，蒲公英或是雏菊，或者...

123
00:12:40,191 --> 00:12:41,602
What daisy?
什么雏菊？

124
00:12:41,734 --> 00:12:43,644
He wants me to grow him a flower.
他想让我为他种朵花

125
00:12:43,737 --> 00:12:45,528
For whom?
为谁啊？
- That's not important. - Pardon.
-那不重要。 -抱歉

126
00:12:45,697 --> 00:12:48,319
Peter.
彼得
- I've got only unicells.
我只有单细胞植物

127
00:12:48,492 --> 00:12:50,366
What if you give her a puppy.
如果你给她一只小狗将会怎么样
- What?
什么？

128
00:12:50,578 --> 00:12:53,247
A puppy, one bitch is in pup.
小狗，一条刚出生的小母狗

129
00:12:53,373 --> 00:12:57,038
I would like something...
我想来点...
- Poetic.
诗意

130
00:12:57,544 --> 00:12:59,252
And what did the astrobiologists bring?
太空生物学家们带来了什么?

131
00:12:59,421 --> 00:13:02,209
Nothing but poetry. Peas, lentils, millet, rice.
除了诗歌什么也没带来. 豌豆，扁豆，小米，大米

132
00:13:02,341 --> 00:13:05,259
Acorns, corn, onions.
橡子，玉米，洋葱
- Sunflower seeds.
向日葵种子

133
00:13:05,511 --> 00:13:10,090
A sunflower is a flower too, isn't it?
向日葵也是一种花，不是吗？

134
00:13:12,978 --> 00:13:16,015
I pull, nothing happens!
我伸展，一切正常！

135
00:13:17,275 --> 00:13:19,683
I pull once more, nothing happens.
我再伸展，一切正常

136
00:13:20,612 --> 00:13:23,103
I'm in hell, you see.
我在地狱里，你明白

137
00:13:24,074 --> 00:13:26,281
I look at the casing thermometer.
我看那个套管温度计呢

138
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:28,035
1,200.

139
00:13:29,163 --> 00:13:31,239
That's big trouble, you see.
真是个大麻烦，你明白

140
00:13:31,457 --> 00:13:33,581
Stop saying you see!
别说“你明白”了！

141
00:13:33,710 --> 00:13:35,952
And do you know what I did?
那么你知道我干了什么吗？

142
00:13:36,338 --> 00:13:39,790
I activated the pulsator. To full power.
我喝了脉动，充满力量

143
00:13:39,967 --> 00:13:42,838
Erik, listen... Twenty kids and a teacher.
艾瑞克，听着...二十个孩子一个老师

144
00:13:42,970 --> 00:13:45,259
I pull one after another! Really quickly,
我一个一个拉他们起来! 非常快，你明白吗?

145
00:13:45,390 --> 00:13:48,261
They're yelling "Mummy"! The teacher too, see?
他们在喊“妈咪”! 老师也喊，你明白?

146
00:13:50,229 --> 00:13:52,268
And what happened next?
然后呢？

147
00:13:56,068 --> 00:13:59,936
That sunflower is ready. Do you still need it?
向日葵已经备好了，你们还要么？

148
00:14:00,073 --> 00:14:02,778
I don't know.
我不知道
- Quite nice.
相当好

149
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:05,697
Who?
谁？
- The sunflower.
向日葵

150
00:14:21,889 --> 00:14:23,966
Let's hope he won't change his mind.
希望他不会改变主意

151
00:14:24,142 --> 00:14:26,182
When I was his age.
当我像他这么大时

152
00:14:28,146 --> 00:14:29,771
Help him.
帮帮他

153
00:14:30,691 --> 00:14:36,944
Sixty. You have a visitor at the door,
Eve. An important visitor.
60号，在你门口有个客人，伊芙， 一个重要的客人

154
00:14:37,741 --> 00:14:39,152
Me?
我吗？

155
00:14:45,499 --> 00:14:47,373
Watch out!
小心！
- Don't be scared.
别害怕

156
00:15:00,099 --> 00:15:03,385
Some flower we've made you, eh?
我们给你做了一些花 呵呵?

157
00:15:04,062 --> 00:15:07,977
Switch it over to the cabin.
切换到客舱
- I can't. It's a private cabin.
- 不行，那是私人客舱

158
00:15:08,525 --> 00:15:11,610
Isn't this a bit imperfect?
是不是有点不完美呢？

159
00:15:11,737 --> 00:15:13,280
On the contrary.
正相反

160
00:15:14,532 --> 00:15:17,202
You won't get away, Anthony.
你不想离开的，安东尼

161
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:20,872
I had one after lunch.
午饭后我又吃了一顿
- You did not.
- 你没有

162
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:23,412
You ran away as usual. Come on.
你像往常一样跑开了，来吧

163
00:15:23,626 --> 00:15:26,378
I had one, ask anyone.
我吃了，问他们

164
00:15:26,880 --> 00:15:29,667
He's telling the truth. He had two.
他说的是事实，他吃了两顿

165
00:15:30,759 --> 00:15:33,001
Yes, two.
是的，两顿
- You don't say!
你别说了

166
00:15:33,470 --> 00:15:36,591
You're all the same. You'll suffer with avitaminosis.
你还是那样，你会得维生素缺乏症的

167
00:15:37,016 --> 00:15:39,258
One has to look after you like a mother.
得有人像母亲一样照顾你

168
00:15:43,732 --> 00:15:46,852
You know I've enjoyed being alone since my childhood.
你知道自从我的童年开始，我就喜欢一个人待着

169
00:15:47,278 --> 00:15:48,902
Brigitte!
布丽奇特!

170
00:15:50,656 --> 00:15:52,982
It seems strange, but I really did.
看上去很奇怪 ，但我的确是那样

171
00:15:53,284 --> 00:15:55,990
I always thought nobody understood me.
我总是认为没有人理解我

172
00:15:56,413 --> 00:15:57,872
Nonsense!
乱讲！

173
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:00,080
Anthony!
安东尼！

174
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:02,412
Can you still see Earth?
你还能看到地球吗?

175
00:16:02,545 --> 00:16:04,787
No.
看不到了
- And the Sun?
那太阳呢？

176
00:16:10,679 --> 00:16:12,921
Humans are like the stars.
人就像这星星

177
00:16:13,724 --> 00:16:15,267
What do you mean?
什么意思？

178
00:16:15,393 --> 00:16:18,145
Somebody orbits around someone else for years.
一个人绕着另外一个人成年累月地转啊转

179
00:16:18,271 --> 00:16:20,311
Who's orbiting?
谁在转？

180
00:16:20,565 --> 00:16:23,021
That was a metaphor.
不过是个比喻罢了
- A metaphor?
比喻？

181
00:16:23,152 --> 00:16:25,394
You're here again?
你又来了？
- Does he come here?
他来了？

182
00:16:25,529 --> 00:16:30,690
Everyday. What else should he do?
He's so lonely, no one understands him.
每天他该做点什么？他太孤独了，没人能理解他

183
00:16:34,081 --> 00:16:36,750
That pin head is the Sun?
那个钉子帽一样的东西是太阳吗?

184
00:16:38,711 --> 00:16:40,538
May I?
我可以继续看么？

185
00:16:40,671 --> 00:16:42,498
Go on.
看吧

186
00:16:53,644 --> 00:16:56,729
Nightly she sings on yon pomegranate tree:
它每天晚上在那边石榴树上歌唱

187
00:16:57,399 --> 00:17:02,227
Believe me, love, it was the nightingale.
相信我，亲爱的，那只是夜莺

188
00:17:03,447 --> 00:17:08,110
It was the lark, the herald of the morn,
那是百灵鸟，是黎明的使者

189
00:17:10,330 --> 00:17:12,702
No nightingale:
不是夜莺

190
00:17:13,417 --> 00:17:19,835
Look, love, what envious streaks do lace
the severing clouds in yonder east:
瞧，亲爱的，不作美的晨曦，已经在东天的云朵上镶起了金线

191
00:17:21,551 --> 00:17:24,636
Night's candles are burnt out, and jocund day
夜晚的蜡烛已经熄灭了，

192
00:17:25,222 --> 00:17:29,137
Stands tiptoe on the misty mountain tops.
愉快的白昼蹑足踏上了迷雾的山巅

193
00:17:33,773 --> 00:17:37,059
Where's Herold?
赫罗尔德在哪？
- On duty. November?
在值班，十一月？

194
00:17:39,279 --> 00:17:40,904
Earth.
地球

195
00:17:41,198 --> 00:17:43,025
What day is it on Earth?
地球上今天是几号?

196
00:17:43,159 --> 00:17:47,074
It was the 18th in the morning and Christmas after lunch.
是18日清晨 ，圣诞节午饭后

197
00:17:48,581 --> 00:17:51,666
They must be celebrating the New Year by now.
当时他们一定在庆祝新年

198
00:17:53,003 --> 00:17:54,795
Time really flies.
时间过得真快啊！

199
00:17:56,591 --> 00:18:00,292
It means I am as old as my youngest sister.
这意味着我和我最小的妹妹一样大

200
00:18:00,762 --> 00:18:02,221
Check!
将军！

201
00:18:03,682 --> 00:18:05,307
It's strange anyway.
反正很奇怪

202
00:18:05,934 --> 00:18:07,761
We're flying to Centauri.
我们在飞往半人马座

203
00:18:07,978 --> 00:18:11,264
Why hasn't anyone ever flown to Earth.
为什么没有人曾飞往地球呢？

204
00:18:11,482 --> 00:18:14,603
Our solar system is of little interest.
我们的太阳系没有什么意思

205
00:18:15,070 --> 00:18:16,695
Play.
走啊

206
00:18:17,322 --> 00:18:20,656
Besides, it's too far from the centre of the Galaxy.
此外，离银河系的中心太远了

207
00:18:20,785 --> 00:18:24,652
26,000 light years. Play!
26,000光年，走！

208
00:18:24,956 --> 00:18:29,702
You see, we're the backwoods of the Universe.
你明白，我们是宇宙的边远地区

209
00:18:53,697 --> 00:18:55,322
Michael!
迈克尔

210
00:18:56,241 --> 00:18:58,281
Are you looking at Alpha?
你在看阿尔法星吗？

211
00:18:59,036 --> 00:19:00,447
Yeah.
是的

212
00:19:01,122 --> 00:19:03,364
I come here often.
我经常来这儿

213
00:19:04,584 --> 00:19:07,585
Do you think they're out there?
你认为他们在那儿吗?

214
00:19:08,630 --> 00:19:11,916
At least on one of the planets. What do you think?
至少在众多行星中的一个之上，你认为呢?

215
00:19:13,719 --> 00:19:17,848
I can't believe that there's life somewhere like on Earth.
我不相信在那里会像地球一样有生命

216
00:19:18,058 --> 00:19:22,601
I mean that we will land there, get out from the ship,
我的意思是我们在那着陆，走出宇宙飞船

217
00:19:22,896 --> 00:19:25,767
and they will run to us, waving their hands.
他们挥舞着手朝我们跑过来

218
00:19:26,275 --> 00:19:28,315
Maybe they don't have them.
或许他们没有手

219
00:19:28,903 --> 00:19:30,943
What? Hands?
什么？手吗？

220
00:19:32,324 --> 00:19:34,281
Do you know that Bernard took his piano with him?
你知道吗？伯纳德把他的钢琴带来了

221
00:19:34,409 --> 00:19:35,820
Why?
为什么啊？

222
00:19:36,161 --> 00:19:40,076
He was in some old music club or something like that, you see.
他在某个老歌俱乐部待过或者有点像那个，你明白

223
00:19:40,208 --> 00:19:43,458
Stop saying you see, you see! Don't say it or else...
别说你明白，你明白的，别再说了，再说...

224
00:19:44,004 --> 00:19:48,334
And stop doing this! Who's supposed
to look at it all the time!
不要再做这件事了!谁期望一直看它!

225
00:19:55,850 --> 00:19:57,475
I'm sorry.
抱歉

226
00:19:57,602 --> 00:20:00,224
I don't know what got into me.
我不知道我是怎么了

227
00:20:02,399 --> 00:20:04,024
No harm done.
没有人受到伤害

228
00:20:07,113 --> 00:20:12,618
When one looks at the same faces for so many months...
当一个人这么成年累月地一直看着同样的面孔..

229
00:20:35,979 --> 00:20:37,723
That is why I summoned the Council.
那就是我为什么召集会议的原因

230
00:20:37,898 --> 00:20:41,314
We could not speak about Stephie's pregnancy before.
我们以前不能讲思戴菲怀孕的事

231
00:20:41,485 --> 00:20:45,531
The crew would become agitated. It is a risky experiment.
机员们会变得焦躁不安，它是一个冒险的实验

232
00:20:45,698 --> 00:20:48,534
None the less, it is essential for future missions.
然而，为了将来的使命，它是不可或缺的

233
00:20:48,744 --> 00:20:51,828
I should have been informed as second-in-command.
我本该被告知做副司令

234
00:20:52,414 --> 00:20:54,787
Explain it to me.
给我解释一下
- Stephie...
思戴菲

235
00:20:57,962 --> 00:21:01,498
Stephie has been already pregnant on Earth.
思戴菲在地球上时就已经怀孕了

236
00:21:01,675 --> 00:21:03,715
That means that my wife...
那意味着我妻子...

237
00:21:04,970 --> 00:21:07,010
could have flown as well.
一样可以飞行

238
00:21:07,682 --> 00:21:09,758
If she knew she could...
假如她知道可以...

239
00:21:10,268 --> 00:21:12,510
Why didn't you tell me?
你为什么不对我讲？

240
00:21:13,647 --> 00:21:15,189
Why?
为什么？

241
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:17,397
Your wife knew it.
你妻子知道这件事

242
00:21:19,403 --> 00:21:20,898
She was afraid.
她害怕了

243
00:21:22,573 --> 00:21:24,650
It will be the first case in history.
这将是历史上的第一案例

244
00:21:25,744 --> 00:21:29,659
No child has ever been born under such circumstances.
没有小孩曾在这种环境下出生

245
00:21:29,790 --> 00:21:32,116
Stephie is ten years younger.
思戴菲比你妻子年轻十岁

246
00:21:32,251 --> 00:21:35,751
That's why your wife gave up her place.
那就是你妻子放弃她的位置的原因

247
00:21:59,532 --> 00:22:00,813
Lightly.
轻轻地

248
00:22:00,950 --> 00:22:02,777
Not so hard.
不要那么猛烈

249
00:22:20,931 --> 00:22:23,173
Something should happen.
有事可能要发生

250
00:22:26,646 --> 00:22:28,769
It's taking too long.
经过太长时间了

251
00:22:30,275 --> 00:22:32,149
Four months.
4个月

252
00:22:32,277 --> 00:22:34,685
We're not even halfway there.
我们甚至走了还不到一半

253
00:22:58,390 --> 00:23:00,549
Where is everybody?
大家在哪儿?

254
00:23:04,147 --> 00:23:07,018
Isn't Kubes here somewhere?
库贝斯没在这儿的某个地方吗?
- No.
- 没有

255
00:23:07,234 --> 00:23:09,689
Nobody has been here lately.
最近没人来过

256
00:23:11,739 --> 00:23:13,778
Why don't you call him through the communicator?
你为什么不用通讯器呼叫他呢?

257
00:23:13,908 --> 00:23:16,695
This way, I can at least take a short walk.
走这边 ，我还能稍微散散步

258
00:23:18,830 --> 00:23:20,870
You're getting bored, eh?
你正在烦恼，是吧？

259
00:23:22,125 --> 00:23:24,664
It's Hopkins's birthday tomorrow.
明天是霍普金斯的生日

260
00:23:26,172 --> 00:23:27,583
Brigitte!
布里奇特!

261
00:23:29,509 --> 00:23:32,961
What's the matter?
出什么事了?
- I don't know what to do.
- 我不知道要做什么

262
00:23:33,472 --> 00:23:38,218
I hadn't worn a skirt for four months
and now, just look at me!
我已经四个月没穿裙子了，现在看看我吧!

263
00:23:38,435 --> 00:23:40,060
Turn around!
转圈!

264
00:23:40,771 --> 00:23:42,396
Walk.
走两步

265
00:23:43,608 --> 00:23:46,479
What did you expect! It turned out really well.
你还要求什么？真得很好看

266
00:23:47,029 --> 00:23:49,068
Do you think he'll like it?
你觉得他会喜欢吗?

267
00:23:50,532 --> 00:23:53,534
Anthony, let us now drink to Patrick!
安东尼 ，让我们为帕特里克干杯!

268
00:23:53,661 --> 00:23:56,235
So that you know that I didn't really mean it then.
这样你就明白，我那时并非真正地针对它

269
00:23:56,372 --> 00:24:01,082
Patrick, that is...
帕特里克 ，就是说...
- Herold. I am on my guard.
- 赫罗尔德 ，我在站岗.

270
00:24:01,211 --> 00:24:02,706
Shut up!
住嘴！
- Herold is here.
- 赫罗尔德来了

271
00:24:02,963 --> 00:24:05,537
I am on my guard.
我在站岗
- What did you teach that robot?
- 你教那个机器人什么了?

272
00:24:05,675 --> 00:24:08,344
I didn't. He learned it himself.
什么都有没有，他自学的

273
00:24:49,683 --> 00:24:50,762
Will you dance?
跳舞吗？

274
00:24:50,892 --> 00:24:53,562
I don't like dancing.
不喜欢
- Neither do I.
我也是

275
00:25:11,749 --> 00:25:13,789
How are you feeling, Stephie?
你觉得怎样，思戴菲？

276
00:26:03,808 --> 00:26:05,848
Give my regards to Stephie.
代我向思戴菲问好

277
00:26:06,853 --> 00:26:11,065
When you come back, I'll be older than you.
当你回来的时候，我会比你老

278
00:26:11,442 --> 00:26:13,684
You won't like me.
你会不喜欢我的

279
00:26:15,238 --> 00:26:17,278
When you come back.
当你回来的时候

280
00:26:21,745 --> 00:26:23,572
I'm thirsty.
我很渴

281
00:26:32,382 --> 00:26:34,956
Oh no, I'm too old for this, my child.
哦不 ，对于跳舞来说我太老了，我的孩子

282
00:26:35,094 --> 00:26:36,968
Eve will teach you.
伊芙会教你
- I will.
我教你

283
00:26:37,096 --> 00:26:40,382
This jiggling is not for me.
这种吉格舞不适合我
- Jiggling, eh?
吉格舞，嗯？

284
00:27:35,620 --> 00:27:39,037
Nina, we...You're a sociologist, aren't you?
妮娜，我们...你是社会学家，对吗?

285
00:27:39,166 --> 00:27:40,744
We have...
我们有...
- Some work for you.
- 一些工作给你

286
00:27:40,876 --> 00:27:43,831
A moral matter.- I see.
- And a social matter.
一个道德上的问题 - 我明白
- 还是一件社会上的问题

287
00:27:43,963 --> 00:27:45,837
The thing is that she's making fun of us.
这个问题就是她在开我们玩笑

288
00:27:45,965 --> 00:27:47,294
Who?
谁？
- Brigitte.
- 布里奇特

289
00:27:47,717 --> 00:27:50,043
At first, she kept obtruding.
首先，她一直困扰着我们
- Obtruding? - Yes.
- 困扰? - 是的

290
00:27:50,179 --> 00:27:52,468
And now she doesn't want to decide which of us to choose.
而现在她不想决定选择我们中的哪一个

291
00:27:52,598 --> 00:27:53,761
That's really interesting.
- It is, isn't it?
那真有趣
- 是的，对吗?

292
00:27:53,891 --> 00:27:58,055
Oh yes. The reason may be that
she has a husband on Earth.
哦，原因可能是她在地球上有丈夫

293
00:28:47,452 --> 00:28:49,029
This is the Master Computer.
这里是主机

294
00:28:49,162 --> 00:28:51,867
Report to your posts immediately!
立刻去你们的岗位报到!

295
00:28:52,666 --> 00:28:56,118
Section commanders report to your headquarters!
各部门指挥官到你们的指挥部报到!

296
00:28:56,754 --> 00:28:59,791
All officers report to the navigation bridge!
全体船员到驾驶桥楼报到!

297
00:29:00,007 --> 00:29:02,713
An object of the 7th order detected
在第二安全区

298
00:29:02,927 --> 00:29:05,964
in the second safety zone!
发现第7号目标!

299
00:29:19,363 --> 00:29:21,819
Somebody turn that terrible noise off!
谁去关掉那该死的噪音!

300
00:29:26,704 --> 00:29:27,985
Distance?
距离?

301
00:29:28,123 --> 00:29:29,498
309.

302
00:29:30,542 --> 00:29:32,416
Angle 17.
角度 17

303
00:29:36,966 --> 00:29:38,758
It may be a comet.
可能是颗彗星

304
00:29:39,052 --> 00:29:40,926
Or a meteor.
或是流星

305
00:29:41,721 --> 00:29:46,847
It may belong to the Alpha Centauri planetary system.
它可能属于阿尔法人马座类行星系

306
00:29:47,478 --> 00:29:52,769
It's the first object from there.
它是来自那儿的第一个天体

307
00:29:52,984 --> 00:29:55,024
What do you need, Anthony?
你需要什么，安东尼

308
00:29:56,238 --> 00:29:57,613
Time.
时间

309
00:30:02,745 --> 00:30:04,287
Here's your comet.
这是你的彗星

310
00:30:04,414 --> 00:30:08,957
Composition: Iron, titanium, germanium
and traces of common elements.
成分: 铁、钛、锗和微量的普通元素

311
00:30:09,419 --> 00:30:12,456
Volume: 57,900 cubic metres.
体积: 57,900

312
00:30:12,590 --> 00:30:16,291
Weight: 15,844 tons.
重量: 15,844吨

313
00:30:17,345 --> 00:30:18,887
Alright, but...
很好，但是

314
00:30:19,014 --> 00:30:21,469
And this is how it looks from a close-up.
这是从特写中它看起来的样子

315
00:30:33,697 --> 00:30:36,318
It contains organic substances.
它里面含有有机体
- That's unbelievable.
- 令人难以置信

316
00:30:36,450 --> 00:30:37,992
And what about signals?
信号怎样?
- No response so far.
- 至今没有反应

317
00:30:38,118 --> 00:30:39,992
Maybe it's an unmanned station.
它有可能是个无人空间站

318
00:30:40,705 --> 00:30:43,825
No, it's a spacecraft. An automatic
station wouldn't be so large.
不，是宇宙飞船，自动空间站不会这么大

319
00:30:43,958 --> 00:30:45,832
It seems primitive.
像是远古的

320
00:30:46,044 --> 00:30:49,912
Just like Ikaria may seem primitive
to them. We know nothing about them.
就像伊卡利号对于它们来说是远古的是一个道理，我们对它们一无所知

321
00:30:51,801 --> 00:30:54,422
Nothing at all.
什么都没有
- But why are they silent?
- 但它们为什么沉默?

322
00:30:54,554 --> 00:30:56,096
They have to see us.
它们应该看到了我们

323
00:30:56,222 --> 00:31:00,684
I don't know. Maybe they're afraid of us.
我不知道，也许他们害怕我们

324
00:31:00,811 --> 00:31:02,436
Afraid?
害怕？

325
00:31:02,563 --> 00:31:07,938
If they are afraid, then they are similar to humans.
如果他们会害怕，他们就跟人类相似了

326
00:31:08,820 --> 00:31:12,521
We can do more than to send the Pythagorean proposition.
我们能做的不只是发送勾股定理

327
00:31:13,992 --> 00:31:15,866
Prepare the explorer shuttle!
准备好探险者航天飞机!

328
00:31:15,995 --> 00:31:18,034
You can't be serious!
不要那么严肃!

329
00:31:18,831 --> 00:31:20,871
What do we have robots for?
我们要让机器人做什么?

330
00:31:22,335 --> 00:31:24,375
What are they for?
- Wait.
它们做什么?
- 等等

331
00:31:25,505 --> 00:31:27,794
Suppose there are living creatures on that ship.
假定在那艘飞船上有生物

332
00:31:27,925 --> 00:31:29,550
Just suppose...
只是假定...

333
00:31:29,677 --> 00:31:34,386
What would we say if they came to us, opened the door,
如果它们朝我们走过来，我们该说什么，打开门

334
00:31:35,016 --> 00:31:37,721
and out came a dozen machines.
从一堆机器中走出来

335
00:31:38,437 --> 00:31:40,311
How would you deal with them?
你们将怎样应付它们?

336
00:31:40,439 --> 00:31:43,476
Try to understand that there are things robots can't do.
试着去理解那些机器人不能做的事情

337
00:31:44,694 --> 00:31:46,734
Humans will be sent to that ship.
派人到那艘飞船上

338
00:31:47,781 --> 00:31:49,572
Two people.
两个人

339
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:52,240
Who do you propose?
你提议谁呢?

340
00:31:57,291 --> 00:31:58,916
Stand at attention, Erik.
立正，埃里克

341
00:31:59,043 --> 00:32:03,421
Peter and me are entering into history.
And not only of mankind.
彼得与我正走进历史，不仅是人类的历史

342
00:32:05,467 --> 00:32:07,425
I've been in a similar situation once.
我也曾有过类似的境遇

343
00:32:07,553 --> 00:32:09,510
I understand.
我明白
- I wanted to give you advice.
- 我想给你们建议

344
00:32:09,639 --> 00:32:12,842
You know more than the Master Computer.
你比主机知道得多

345
00:32:13,059 --> 00:32:15,764
I've always thought it didn't exist any more.
我总是觉得它不再存在了

346
00:32:15,896 --> 00:32:17,520
What?
什么?

347
00:32:18,816 --> 00:32:23,692
I don't know, but I envy you.
不知道，不过我羡慕你们

348
00:32:57,026 --> 00:32:59,065
The explorer shuttle is ready.
探险者航天飞机准备就绪

349
00:33:00,863 --> 00:33:01,895
Launch.
发射

350
00:33:15,713 --> 00:33:17,089
Launch complete.
发射完毕

351
00:33:47,416 --> 00:33:49,623
Well?
怎样？
- Everything's alright.
- 一切正常

352
00:33:49,835 --> 00:33:51,875
Activate screen transmission.
激活屏幕传输

353
00:33:52,004 --> 00:33:54,875
We'll keep on trying to establish contact with the spaceship.
我们要继续试着与宇宙飞船保持联络

354
00:33:57,093 --> 00:34:01,139
It's silent. They may have different communication methods.
它寂静无声，或许它们用的是不同的通讯方式

355
00:34:36,972 --> 00:34:39,012
Maybe it's a wreck.
或许是失事船的残骸

356
00:34:40,726 --> 00:34:42,766
Do we have permission to land?
我们得到降落的许可了吗?

357
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:46,936
Guide the shuttle forlanding.
操纵航天飞机着陆

358
00:36:32,603 --> 00:36:36,471
We are entering the craft. There's vacuum here.
我们正进入航天器，这儿是真空的

359
00:37:11,230 --> 00:37:13,270
Do you see the material?
你看到那东西了吗?

360
00:37:13,733 --> 00:37:16,520
It looks like some sort of aluminium alloy.
看起来像某种铝合金

361
00:37:16,694 --> 00:37:18,521
Prehistoric.
史前的

362
00:37:35,257 --> 00:37:38,709
I thought we would find something worthwhile here.
我想我们会在这儿找到一些有价值的东西

363
00:37:42,849 --> 00:37:44,308
Look.
看

364
00:37:44,768 --> 00:37:47,852
A number. It's from Earth.
数字，是来自地球的

365
00:37:48,730 --> 00:37:52,645
Nonsense, this can couldn't fly out here.
胡说，这个金属容器不可能飞到这儿

366
00:38:01,578 --> 00:38:03,405
Money?
钱?

367
00:38:09,003 --> 00:38:12,455
Those are... Those were humans.
那些是...那些是人类

368
00:38:13,467 --> 00:38:15,625
We found humans, Captain Abayev.
我们发现了人，阿巴耶夫机长

369
00:38:15,761 --> 00:38:17,220
Humans?
人类?

370
00:38:17,388 --> 00:38:21,516
It's an ancient rocket from Earth.
是一只来自地球的古代火箭

371
00:38:21,726 --> 00:38:23,766
From which century?
来自哪个世纪?

372
00:38:24,938 --> 00:38:29,186
I don't know. Maybe the 20th according to their clothes.
不知道，通过他们的衣服来看可能是20世纪的

373
00:38:29,485 --> 00:38:33,815
We found cigarettes, glass, paper.
我们找到了香烟，玻璃制品，纸

374
00:38:34,282 --> 00:38:36,191
The women are wearing jewellery.
女人们戴着首饰

375
00:38:41,040 --> 00:38:43,709
They all died at the same moment.
他们在同一时刻死去

376
00:38:44,085 --> 00:38:46,541
How? How did they die?
怎么? 他们是怎么死的?

377
00:38:47,172 --> 00:38:51,122
I don't know. Everything is intact.
我不知道，每件东西都完好无损

378
00:38:51,718 --> 00:38:54,636
They look as if they had fallen asleep.
他们看起来像是睡着了

379
00:38:54,763 --> 00:38:59,058
Find out who they are and how did they get out here.
查明他们是谁，还有他们是怎么到得这儿

380
00:39:00,019 --> 00:39:02,890
You should have sent an archaeologist instead.
你本该派一个考古学家

381
00:39:17,790 --> 00:39:21,918
Tigger, Tigger Fun.
迪歌，迪歌番

382
00:39:22,753 --> 00:39:24,830
Herold to Ikaria.
赫罗尔德对伊卡利号讲话

383
00:39:24,964 --> 00:39:29,342
Find out what Tigger Fun means, Eve.
查出迪歌番是什么意思，伊芙

384
00:39:50,118 --> 00:39:51,660
Look, Nina.
妮娜，快看

385
00:39:52,203 --> 00:39:54,695
Tor-na-do.
托-纳-多

386
00:39:58,919 --> 00:40:01,292
Nineteen eighty seven.
19  80  7

387
00:40:03,341 --> 00:40:05,667
Complete. We have first data.
完毕，我们有第一手资料

388
00:40:05,844 --> 00:40:07,671
Master Computer.
主机

389
00:40:08,889 --> 00:40:12,175
Tigger Fun, also tiger breath.
迪歌番，也就是老虎气息

390
00:40:12,309 --> 00:40:15,975
Deadly poison with immediate effect.
即刻发作的致命毒药

391
00:40:16,564 --> 00:40:18,688
Does not cause deterioration of objects.
不会引起物体变质

392
00:40:19,317 --> 00:40:24,657
The so-called clean weapon from the end of the 20th century.
是一种来自于20世纪末的纯净武器

393
00:40:25,199 --> 00:40:28,403
Tornado, a type of a military missile.
托纳多，一种军事导弹的型式

394
00:40:28,703 --> 00:40:31,954
No further data available, stop.
没有更多的资料可用了，停止

395
00:40:33,584 --> 00:40:36,668
They wanted to get to another planet.
他们想到另一颗行星上

396
00:40:49,268 --> 00:40:52,353
Overthere. There's light there.
那儿，那儿有灯光

397
00:40:56,860 --> 00:41:00,146
Caution, the ship still has power.
小心，这只飞船上面还有电
- That's not possible.
- 不可能

398
00:41:02,616 --> 00:41:06,911
Why not? A reactor can work a hundred years without operators.
为什么不? 核反应堆在无控制的情况下可以运行100年

399
00:41:21,638 --> 00:41:23,263
A general.
一名将军

400
00:41:29,146 --> 00:41:30,973
He was in command.
他是指挥官

401
00:41:38,657 --> 00:41:40,697
There's two of them.
另外两个

402
00:41:41,285 --> 00:41:43,693
Look he has a back wound.
看，他后背有伤

403
00:41:43,830 --> 00:41:47,745
When they were running low on oxygen,
they killed the crew with Tigger Fun,
当他们处于低氧的状态时，他们就用迪歌番杀死了机员

404
00:41:47,876 --> 00:41:49,620
so that they would survive longer.
以便他们能活得更久些

405
00:41:49,753 --> 00:41:52,291
In the end, they fought one another.
最后他们互相厮打

406
00:41:52,423 --> 00:41:54,250
Vultures.
贪婪的人们

407
00:42:11,987 --> 00:42:16,115
I must be somewhere near the engines. I'll find out.
我一定是在发动机附近的某个地方，我去找一下

408
00:42:26,086 --> 00:42:28,328
What is it Kubes? Answer!
库贝斯，那是什么？请回答!

409
00:42:29,506 --> 00:42:34,169
Herold! Help Kubes, quick!
赫罗尔德! 快去帮帮库贝斯!
- The radioactivity level is increasing.
- 放射线的级别正在增大

410
00:42:34,554 --> 00:42:37,638
What happened, Kubes? Answer!
发生了什么事，库贝斯? 请回答!

411
00:42:39,142 --> 00:42:42,428
At the right, that's from Kubes's camera.
在右边，那是库贝斯摄像机的方向

412
00:42:43,731 --> 00:42:45,771
But that looks like...
但那看起来像...

413
00:42:54,535 --> 00:42:56,991
You always get yourself into trouble.
你总是使自己陷入麻烦之中

414
00:42:57,663 --> 00:43:00,949
My magnetic boot got caught.
我的一只磁力靴被吸住了

415
00:43:03,378 --> 00:43:05,834
Look, overthere!
看，那边

416
00:43:10,970 --> 00:43:13,426
Abandon the ship, quick!
离开那艘飞船，快!

417
00:43:13,765 --> 00:43:15,758
There are nuclear weapons on board!
上面有核武器!

418
00:43:15,892 --> 00:43:17,932
Don't touch anything!
不要碰任何东西!

419
00:43:23,901 --> 00:43:26,143
Come on, hurry!
跟上，快!

420
00:43:27,113 --> 00:43:29,984
Send them the engine module, Svenson.
史文森，送他们到引擎舱

421
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:57,761
Distance 3,458 kilometres.
距离3,458公里
- The shuttle is ready to lift off.
- 航天飞机正准备起飞

422
00:44:02,695 --> 00:44:06,396
Don't stop! Don't touch anything! Hurry!
别停下! 别碰任何东西! 赶快!

423
00:44:07,450 --> 00:44:09,075
Run!
跑！

424
00:45:16,987 --> 00:45:21,946
We found people, Captain Abayev, we found people.
我找到了人类，阿巴耶夫机长，我找到了人类

425
00:45:23,662 --> 00:45:26,948
We discovered the 20th century.
我发现了20世纪

426
00:45:56,741 --> 00:45:58,983
Would you send them there again?
你会再派他们去那儿吗?

427
00:46:01,246 --> 00:46:04,746
If I knew there weren't any humans there.
假如我知道那儿没有任何人类

428
00:46:09,672 --> 00:46:11,499
Humans...
人类...

429
00:46:20,017 --> 00:46:22,057
They were our ancestors.
他们是我们的祖先

430
00:46:22,353 --> 00:46:24,013
Not them.
他们不是

431
00:46:25,356 --> 00:46:26,981
Definitely not them!
很明显他们不是

432
00:46:28,235 --> 00:46:30,524
You can't choose your ancestors.
你不能选择你的祖先

433
00:46:33,365 --> 00:46:35,239
You know who they were?
你知道他们是谁?

434
00:46:35,868 --> 00:46:37,244
Human trash.
人渣

435
00:46:38,163 --> 00:46:42,492
That left Auschwitz, Oradour
他们遗留下了奥斯威辛集中营，奥拉都尔

436
00:46:43,710 --> 00:46:45,584
and Hiroshima behind them.
还有广岛

437
00:46:46,797 --> 00:46:48,921
The 20th century.
20世纪

438
00:46:51,886 --> 00:46:53,678
Do you know it?
你知道它吗?

439
00:46:57,226 --> 00:46:59,017
Honegger.
霍涅格

440
00:47:03,316 --> 00:47:05,523
Also the 20th century.
也是20世纪

441
00:47:18,500 --> 00:47:20,789
We had to continue in our journey.
我们得继续我们的旅程

442
00:47:21,670 --> 00:47:27,045
Svenson and Michael were to supervise
the installation of a reserve engine.
史文森和米迦勒去指导预备引擎的安装

443
00:47:28,344 --> 00:47:32,806
During such work they have to go out
into space on Ikaria's surface.
在此工作的整个期间，他们得进入太空到伊卡利号的的表面上

444
00:47:33,934 --> 00:47:37,979
They weren't there long, only some ten or fifteen minutes.
他们不能长时间呆在外面，只能大约10或15分钟

445
00:47:38,439 --> 00:47:42,733
Under normal circumstances, this would be an insignificant episode.
在正常环境下，这是一件微不足道的事情

446
00:47:43,278 --> 00:47:49,898
Thus, no one knew that this moment was
the beginning of lethal danger to us.
这种情况下，没有人知道这一刻
对于我们是致命危险的开端

447
00:47:50,786 --> 00:47:53,408
It entered into Ikaria with them.
它与他们进入到伊卡利

448
00:47:59,797 --> 00:48:02,418
How does it look out there, Erik?
从那儿往外，看起来怎样，埃里克?

449
00:48:03,884 --> 00:48:07,171
Alright.
很好
- The robots will do the rest.
- 机器人来做余下的工作

450
00:48:18,484 --> 00:48:20,773
That's Alpha Centauri.
那就是半人马座阿尔法星

451
00:48:21,237 --> 00:48:24,773
There must be at least two planets in the ecosphere.
在生态层里，那儿肯定至少有两颗行星

452
00:48:25,993 --> 00:48:28,033
In the sphere of life.
在生命的领域里

453
00:48:28,162 --> 00:48:29,787
Do you think so?
你这么认为吗?

454
00:48:29,997 --> 00:48:32,868
I know, I calculated it.
我知道，我计算过

455
00:48:33,251 --> 00:48:37,036
Yet, the temperature will be high
on both the planets, like on our Venus.
然而，这两颗行星的温度可能很高
像在我们的金星上面

456
00:48:37,172 --> 00:48:39,046
But life could be there, because...
但那上面不可能存在生命，因为...

457
00:48:39,174 --> 00:48:42,045
I'm not a prophet, I'm a mathematician.
我不是预言家，我是数学家

458
00:48:42,261 --> 00:48:45,132
We will find out in...
我们将在...查明
- In fifty-six days.
- 56天之后

459
00:48:45,932 --> 00:48:47,806
Precisely.
确切地说

460
00:48:51,522 --> 00:48:52,897
Milek...
米尔克...

461
00:48:55,026 --> 00:48:56,650
It's normal.
正常

462
00:48:58,530 --> 00:49:00,736
Will you have a girl or a boy?
你想要个男孩还是女孩?

463
00:49:00,866 --> 00:49:02,146
A boy.
男孩

464
00:49:02,618 --> 00:49:05,489
How will you name him?
你怎么给他取名?

465
00:49:05,704 --> 00:49:07,080
Wait.
等等

466
00:49:07,206 --> 00:49:08,831
Wait...
等等

467
00:49:09,626 --> 00:49:11,665
Do you know which name is really nice?
你知道哪个名字够好?

468
00:49:12,462 --> 00:49:14,087
Michael.
迈克尔

469
00:49:14,631 --> 00:49:16,256
Anthony!
安东尼

470
00:49:16,884 --> 00:49:18,164
Anthony!
安东尼

471
00:49:19,387 --> 00:49:21,011
Listen.
听

472
00:49:37,490 --> 00:49:39,779
A radio nebula.
无线电星云

473
00:49:46,584 --> 00:49:48,043
Grandpa has caught a nebula again.
外公曾两次撞见过星云

474
00:49:48,253 --> 00:49:50,708
Golly, are we supposed to survey every smudge?
天呀，我们该研究每个污点吗?

475
00:49:50,839 --> 00:49:53,959
Yes. Every single one.
是的，每一个

476
00:49:55,844 --> 00:50:02,975
Alert! Third deck! Lying person! Non-responding person!
警报! 第三甲板! 躺着的人! 无反应的人!

477
00:50:04,187 --> 00:50:06,061
That can't be possible.
不可能的

478
00:50:06,356 --> 00:50:12,063
Alert! Non-responding person!
警报! 无反应的人!

479
00:50:12,530 --> 00:50:15,484
Who is it?
那是谁?
- Dead person! Dead person!
- 死人! 死人!

480
00:50:15,700 --> 00:50:17,159
Michael.
迈克尔

481
00:50:17,369 --> 00:50:20,156
Dead person! Dead person!
死人! 死人!

482
00:50:38,309 --> 00:50:41,844
I...I must have fallen asleep.
我...我一定是睡着了

483
00:50:42,230 --> 00:50:43,855
Well, well.
好啊，好啊

484
00:50:47,319 --> 00:50:50,855
I was on my way from the observatory
and all of a sudden...
我在离开瞭望台的路上，突然...

485
00:50:50,990 --> 00:50:53,113
And that stupid computer thought...
那台愚蠢的计算机认为...

486
00:50:53,410 --> 00:50:56,031
Never mind the computer, I thought so too.
不关计算机的事，我也这么想的

487
00:50:57,080 --> 00:50:59,204
Dead person on board.
飞船上的死人

488
00:51:04,005 --> 00:51:05,879
And it will be surrounded by a large garden.
它会被一个大花园包围

489
00:51:06,007 --> 00:51:08,047
Without paths?
没有小路?

490
00:51:10,095 --> 00:51:13,547
There will be grass everywhere, very high grass.
到处都是绿草，非常高的那种

491
00:51:16,436 --> 00:51:20,304
Report it next time or the computer
will take you as dead with no lunch.
下次要报告，否则计算机该把你当成没吃午饭的死人了

492
00:51:20,774 --> 00:51:22,897
I don't know how it could happen.
我不知道那是如何发生的

493
00:51:23,026 --> 00:51:25,066
I knew one geologist once.
我曾认识一个地质学家

494
00:51:25,446 --> 00:51:28,566
He fell asleep on an asteroid.
他在一棵小行星上睡着了

495
00:51:28,866 --> 00:51:30,491
On asteroid 608.
在608号行星上

496
00:51:30,785 --> 00:51:33,905
Gosh, the whole zone was on alert thinking he went missing.
啊，整个区的人都警觉的认为他走失了

497
00:51:36,709 --> 00:51:38,998
At least 150 ships were looking for him.
至少150艘飞船找他

498
00:51:39,128 --> 00:51:43,173
And I'm not counting unmanned crafts.
我没把无人驾驶的航天器计算在内

499
00:51:49,640 --> 00:51:51,680
I will lie on my back
我想躺下

500
00:51:52,560 --> 00:51:54,766
and look at the clouds.
看那上面的白云

501
00:51:55,730 --> 00:52:00,024
Ants will be crawling on the grass.
蚂蚁在草地上爬行
- And it will start raining.
- 天开始下雨

502
00:52:01,570 --> 00:52:04,856
But we won't run for shelter, will we? We will stay outside.
我们不用跑去避雨，是吗? 我们就在外面待着

503
00:52:05,157 --> 00:52:07,446
Raindrops will be running down our neck.
雨滴顺着我们的脖颈而下

504
00:52:12,499 --> 00:52:14,124
Erik!
埃里克!

505
00:52:16,170 --> 00:52:18,210
I'm telling you I'm alright.
我告诉你们我没事了

506
00:52:19,674 --> 00:52:21,880
I've never needed this all my life.
我一辈子都不要这个

507
00:52:23,094 --> 00:52:25,799
And I'll never need it!
我绝不会用它!
- Very well, go.
- 很好，走吧

508
00:52:30,770 --> 00:52:32,727
It is not a disease.
它不是一种疾病

509
00:52:33,940 --> 00:52:35,980
I'm doing what I can.
我将尽我所能去做

510
00:52:36,109 --> 00:52:39,395
What about biological separation from Earth?
与地球的生物分离怎么样?

511
00:52:39,780 --> 00:52:42,817
That's out of the question nowadays.
时下是不可能的
- And time dilatation?
- 时间流逝变慢效应?

512
00:52:43,034 --> 00:52:45,489
That's an abstract theory, mathematical.
这是个抽象的理论，数学上的

513
00:52:45,620 --> 00:52:47,577
Will it continue?
它将继续吗?

514
00:52:51,043 --> 00:52:53,914
Is it dead?
它死了吗?
- Sleeping.
- 睡觉呢

515
00:52:58,217 --> 00:53:01,918
Stephie, honey, what's wrong with you?
思戴菲，宝贝，你怎么了？

516
00:53:02,639 --> 00:53:06,340
Nothing. Leave me alone.
没事，别管我
- Do they know anything?
- 你知道什么？

517
00:53:07,394 --> 00:53:09,186
And the doctor?
医生？

518
00:53:10,648 --> 00:53:12,855
What if the baby...
如果婴儿...

519
00:53:21,827 --> 00:53:25,778
We did not know what was happening to us.
我不知道我们会遭遇什么

520
00:53:26,249 --> 00:53:28,705
We were not able to cope with it,
我们应付不了

521
00:53:28,835 --> 00:53:32,703
the fatigue, the drowsiness.
疲劳，困倦

522
00:53:33,257 --> 00:53:36,543
We were forced to activate more and more automatons
我们不得不去让越来越多的机器活动起来

523
00:53:36,678 --> 00:53:40,129
to keep Ikaria running normally.
以保持伊卡利号正常运转

524
00:53:41,016 --> 00:53:43,721
It was then when Hopkins revealed
那时，霍普金斯透露

525
00:53:44,186 --> 00:53:47,472
that while focusing the telescope,
就在他调节望远镜的时候

526
00:53:47,940 --> 00:53:52,733
several stars kept disappearing and reappearing.
几颗星星一直忽隐忽现

527
00:53:54,281 --> 00:54:01,163
There was something between them and the Ikaria.
在它们和伊卡利号之间有某些物体

528
00:54:01,539 --> 00:54:03,995
A gigantic body.
一个巨大的天体

529
00:54:04,209 --> 00:54:08,503
A Dark Star, to be more precise.
更确切地说，是一个黑色星球。

530
00:54:09,548 --> 00:54:15,172
We didn't have the slightest idea
of its existence until then.
直到那时，我们才对
它的存在有了一个极小的概念

531
00:54:15,889 --> 00:54:20,017
It came to light that the nature of its radiation...
它的放射性质为人所知

532
00:54:20,561 --> 00:54:24,938
The nature ofits radiation is simply beyond anything we know.
它的放射线性质完全超出了我们的所知范畴

533
00:54:25,149 --> 00:54:27,771
It is certain that its radiation causes
肯定是它的放射线引起的

534
00:54:27,902 --> 00:54:30,939
attenuation of biochemical processes in living organisms.
生物活体的生化过程的衰减

535
00:54:31,406 --> 00:54:34,360
Inducing fatigue and drowsiness.
包括疲劳和困倦
- Where is it?
- 它在哪儿?

536
00:54:35,911 --> 00:54:38,118
How long will the effect last?
这种影响会持续多久?

537
00:54:38,247 --> 00:54:41,284
We don't know that. Or do we?
我们不知道，是吗?

538
00:54:43,587 --> 00:54:49,626
Here are 14,000 metres of reports from
labs, the observatory, astrobiologists.
这是来自实验室 ，天文台
太空生物学者们的14,000公尺报告

539
00:54:49,927 --> 00:54:54,471
Some of them are the first of their
kind and Earth has no idea about them.
它们中一些性质是首次面世，地球对它们一无所知

540
00:54:54,933 --> 00:54:58,385
What now? Will we send them to Earth?
现在怎么样?  我们把它们送到地球?

541
00:54:58,854 --> 00:55:03,232
What for? Why should we worry them for nothing?
为什么?  我们为什么要为它们做无谓的担心呢?

542
00:55:05,695 --> 00:55:07,902
But what if we don't come back?
但如果我们不回来的话会怎样呢?

543
00:55:08,448 --> 00:55:10,073
Nonsense.
胡说

544
00:55:10,701 --> 00:55:15,078
It's hard to believe that a star
could affect the fate of our mission.
难以置信，一颗星星能影响我们任务的命运

545
00:55:15,372 --> 00:55:18,327
But Earth knows nothing about the Dark Star.
但地球对黑色星球一无所知

546
00:55:19,127 --> 00:55:22,164
The next mission would encounter it again.
下一次任务将会重蹈覆辙

547
00:55:25,801 --> 00:55:30,428
It will be better if we do it.
如果我们做了的话，事情就会好些
- Alright.
- 好吧

548
00:55:30,556 --> 00:55:34,341
In the old days, castaways used to throw bottles into the sea.
从前，坐船遇难者常常向海里投放瓶子

549
00:55:36,063 --> 00:55:38,269
We will send a module.
我们将发射一个元件

550
00:55:38,732 --> 00:55:41,188
Yet are we castaways?
我们已经是遇难者了?

551
00:56:16,358 --> 00:56:20,570
Try to understand, if we all fall asleep it will take decades
试着体会一下，假如我们都睡着了，在人们到那儿之前

552
00:56:20,863 --> 00:56:23,734
before people get there, where we are right now.
到达我们现在正处的地方，将会花费几十年

553
00:56:27,204 --> 00:56:29,446
We're not on a holiday cruise!
我们不是在度假旅行!

554
00:56:30,124 --> 00:56:32,959
Each of us knew what he was in for!
我们每人都知道他一定遭遇到什么了!
- Stop yelling.
别吼了

555
00:56:33,085 --> 00:56:39,967
Alert! Second deck! Non-responding person, dead person!
警报! 第二甲板!无反应的人，死人!

556
00:56:44,306 --> 00:56:47,592
I want tough men here. That's all.
我需要强壮的男人到这儿，就这样

557
00:56:48,770 --> 00:56:51,226
You can't blame anyone for this.
你不能因此责怪任何人

558
00:56:53,483 --> 00:56:55,891
I know, but...
我知道，但是...

559
00:56:58,322 --> 00:57:00,648
Those who want, will survive.
那些走的人，将幸免于难

560
00:57:02,118 --> 00:57:04,158
And those who don't...
而那些没走的...

561
00:57:10,127 --> 00:57:11,752
Michael.
迈克尔

562
00:57:19,721 --> 00:57:21,880
When I know that it's a disease,
当我知道它是一种疾病时

563
00:57:22,266 --> 00:57:25,137
that it has a name, I will respect it.
知道它有名字，我重视它

564
00:57:25,269 --> 00:57:28,140
Until then, it doesn't exist for us.
在那之前，对于我们来说，它是不存在的

565
00:57:30,108 --> 00:57:31,935
Is that clear?
明白了吗？

566
00:57:42,581 --> 00:57:45,286
They insisted that nothing new
他们坚持认为，在宇宙中

567
00:57:45,417 --> 00:57:50,294
could be discovered in the Universe.
不会发现任何新事物

568
00:58:00,142 --> 00:58:03,013
They've been proclaiming that for 300 years.
他们那样宣称已经有300年了

569
00:58:06,149 --> 00:58:07,976
Fools.
傻逼们

570
00:58:19,456 --> 00:58:21,283
But it can.
但它能

571
00:58:24,837 --> 00:58:26,664
It can.
它能

572
00:58:30,510 --> 00:58:33,381
Why... Why couldn't it.
为什么...它为什么不能

573
00:58:34,097 --> 00:58:35,508
Anthony!
安东尼!

574
00:58:36,266 --> 00:58:39,184
How long will it take us to get out of this?
脱离它要花费我们多长时间?

575
00:58:39,311 --> 00:58:41,767
Anthony! Do you hear me?
安东尼!  你听到没有?

576
00:58:44,609 --> 00:58:47,694
Sixty hours.
60小时

577
00:58:47,821 --> 00:58:49,648
And then?
然后呢?

578
00:58:52,284 --> 00:58:54,112
And then?
然后呢?

579
00:58:55,038 --> 00:58:58,122
I don't know what will happen then.
我不知道接着会发生什么

580
00:59:00,168 --> 00:59:03,004
Will we wake up? Do you believe it?
我们会醒来吗? 你信仰它吗?

581
00:59:03,130 --> 00:59:05,456
I believe it.
我信
- It's not about belief.
这无关信仰

582
00:59:06,050 --> 00:59:08,720
Belief is nothing. Belief is a mere word.
信仰什么也不是，信仰仅仅是一个词

583
00:59:08,845 --> 00:59:11,087
Tell me how to endure.
告诉我怎么去忍耐

584
00:59:12,015 --> 00:59:13,510
Tell me when and how will we wake up.
告诉我我们何时、怎样醒来

585
00:59:13,642 --> 00:59:18,186
What is the probability, what certainty. That's my belief. Understand?
什么是概率，什么是确定性
那才是我的信仰，明白吗?

586
00:59:20,566 --> 00:59:24,695
Prepare for 60 hours of sleep.
准备好60个小时的睡眠

587
00:59:32,079 --> 00:59:34,119
Is that all we know?
那就是我们知道的所有事情?

588
00:59:43,301 --> 00:59:45,128
Where are you going?
你要去哪儿?

589
00:59:45,720 --> 00:59:47,760
To get the Ikaria back.
去把伊卡利号弄回来

590
00:59:50,642 --> 00:59:54,059
You think I'm afraid.
你认为我害怕了

591
00:59:56,732 --> 01:00:02,107
No, I'm not afraid.
不，我不害怕

592
01:00:02,697 --> 01:00:04,322
Honestly.
说实话

593
01:00:05,701 --> 01:00:07,326
I'd just...
我只是...

594
01:00:08,245 --> 01:00:10,404
I'd just love to hear
我只是喜欢听

595
01:00:11,666 --> 01:00:14,952
those words, you know.
那些话，你知道的

596
01:00:15,670 --> 01:00:18,126
That we made up together.
让我们团结起来

597
01:00:20,551 --> 01:00:23,007
Nobody knows them here.
没人知道

598
01:00:23,972 --> 01:00:26,261
Nobody knows that...
没人知道...

599
01:00:26,641 --> 01:00:30,770
I am your twinklet. And your...
我是你的光芒，你的...

600
01:00:33,899 --> 01:00:37,945
No, I really don't have to be brave.
不，我真的不需要变得勇敢

601
01:00:40,323 --> 01:00:42,993
I will only fall asleep.
我只想睡一觉

602
01:00:48,666 --> 01:00:51,537
You will hear me when I wake up.
我醒来时，你会听到我的声音

603
01:00:54,381 --> 01:00:57,881
It may take long before you find us.
你可能要花很长时间才能找到我们

604
01:00:58,928 --> 01:01:00,968
Maybe you won't...
或许你不会...

605
01:01:02,557 --> 01:01:07,848
No, you will hear me.
不，你会听到我的

606
01:01:10,566 --> 01:01:14,695
One day... You will hear me.
总有一天...你会听到我的

607
01:01:20,911 --> 01:01:24,411
I am glad I went on this mission.
能参加这次任务，我很高兴

608
01:01:28,127 --> 01:01:32,457
Only those sweet words.
只有那些甜言蜜语

609
01:01:33,133 --> 01:01:38,555
Those words you made up for me
你为我编造的那些话语

610
01:01:40,642 --> 01:01:44,343
that nobody knew here.
在这儿没人知道

611
01:01:44,771 --> 01:01:50,228
Master Computer. Message for Earth recorded.
主机，为地球记录的信息

612
01:01:55,367 --> 01:01:57,406
I will get her back.
我会让她回来

613
01:01:58,620 --> 01:02:00,613
She will fly alone.
她将去独自飞行

614
01:02:01,040 --> 01:02:03,282
Back to the Sun.
回到太阳上

615
01:02:04,627 --> 01:02:06,454
They will find her.
他们会找到她

616
01:02:21,271 --> 01:02:23,311
I must get her back.
我必须让她回来

617
01:02:47,217 --> 01:02:48,842
MacDonald!
麦克唐纳

618
01:02:50,763 --> 01:02:52,802
You don't have the right.
你没有那个权利

619
01:02:54,558 --> 01:02:56,598
You don't have the right! Do you understand?
你没有那个权利，你明白吗？

620
01:02:57,353 --> 01:02:59,560
This is our last chance.
这是我们最后的机会

621
01:03:02,442 --> 01:03:04,768
I want to save the Ikaria.
我想拯救伊卡利号

622
01:03:14,623 --> 01:03:17,624
But we will wake up.
但是我们会醒来

623
01:03:22,423 --> 01:03:24,048
Believe it.
相信它

624
01:03:29,431 --> 01:03:31,839
We will wake up.
我们会醒来

625
01:04:15,567 --> 01:04:19,612
Master Computer proceeds with the autoregulation process.
主机利用自动调节程序继续运行

626
01:04:19,738 --> 01:04:23,357
End of first shift. Second shift unmanned.
第一次转换结束，第二次无人转换

627
01:04:23,826 --> 01:04:28,489
Attention, third shift must intake the vitamin condensate.
注意，第三次转换，必须摄入维生素浓缩物

628
01:04:28,707 --> 01:04:30,783
Do not take fruit.
不能吃水果

629
01:05:01,661 --> 01:05:03,700
Anthony.
安东尼

630
01:05:04,581 --> 01:05:06,620
Anthony.
安东尼

631
01:05:56,014 --> 01:06:00,261
End of third shift.
First shift unmanned.
第三次转换结束，第一次无人转换

632
01:06:00,435 --> 01:06:04,979
Master Computer proceeds with the autoregulation process.
主机利用自动调节程序继续运行

633
01:06:05,733 --> 01:06:07,525
Normal regime.
正常的生活规律

634
01:06:18,831 --> 01:06:20,658
Good morning.
早上好

635
01:06:36,351 --> 01:06:38,391
Everything is alright.
一切正常

636
01:06:41,440 --> 01:06:43,065
It isn't.
不正常

637
01:06:43,526 --> 01:06:46,100
We slept only twenty-five hours.
我们仅仅睡了25个小时

638
01:06:46,237 --> 01:06:48,064
Not sixty.
不是60

639
01:07:06,176 --> 01:07:07,801
Eve!
伊芙！

640
01:07:22,904 --> 01:07:24,528
Stephie!
思戴菲！

641
01:07:26,449 --> 01:07:28,074
Stephie.
思戴菲

642
01:07:39,714 --> 01:07:40,995
That's the only explanation.
那是唯一的解释

643
01:07:41,133 --> 01:07:45,510
Some kind of a force field was generated
between the Ikaria and the Dark Star.
伊卡利跟黑色星球之间产生了某种力场

644
01:07:45,638 --> 01:07:46,883
Eat!
吃饭！

645
01:07:47,014 --> 01:07:50,099
A force field that intercepted the radiation.
力场中断了放射线

646
01:07:50,226 --> 01:07:52,896
That's why we woke up earlier.
这就是我们能比较早醒来的原因
- Eat, Anthony.
- 吃饭，安东尼

647
01:07:53,063 --> 01:07:54,308
What?
什么？
- Eat!
- 吃饭！

648
01:07:54,439 --> 01:07:56,847
I think there must be a more simple explanation.
我认为一定，有一种更简单的放射线

649
01:07:56,984 --> 01:07:59,654
Our organism simply got accustomed to it.
我们的机体完全地适应它了

650
01:07:59,779 --> 01:08:03,480
Accustomed? It got accustomed to
radiation in just a few hours, eh?
适应?  仅仅适应了几个小时，嗯?

651
01:08:03,867 --> 01:08:05,906
Perhaps your organism did.
或许你的机体适应了

652
01:08:06,203 --> 01:08:10,450
Mine can't even get used to this mash all the way.
我的机体甚至完全不习惯于这种糊状物

653
01:08:12,835 --> 01:08:15,836
You'll suffer with avitaminosis.
你会得维生素缺乏症的
- Beware, though.
- 还是要当心

654
01:08:16,214 --> 01:08:19,630
Where did the force field that protected us come from?
保护我们的力场是从哪儿来的呢?

655
01:08:21,011 --> 01:08:23,004
Maybe it's just a coincidence, Anthony.
或许只是巧合，安东尼

656
01:08:23,180 --> 01:08:24,295
Coincidence?
巧合？

657
01:08:24,473 --> 01:08:28,554
Coincidence exists among us humans, but not among the stars.
巧合存在于我们人类之中，但不会存在于星球之中

658
01:08:28,937 --> 01:08:30,597
Finish your meal.
把你的饭吃完

659
01:08:31,064 --> 01:08:33,982
The main thing is we got out of it without consequences.
主要的事情就是，我们要避免它没有结果

660
01:08:34,109 --> 01:08:38,522
Just imagine mankind would have sent
Ikaria on this mission without a crew.
就请想象一下，人类将派没有机员的伊卡利执行任务

661
01:08:38,698 --> 01:08:40,904
It would be on her way back.
它在返程的路上

662
01:08:41,075 --> 01:08:43,448
The automatons would have turned it back.
自动装置将使它返回

663
01:08:43,620 --> 01:08:47,665
Fortunately, man is not as perfect as a machine.
幸运的是，人不如机器完美

664
01:08:48,667 --> 01:08:52,962
Therefore, he has nothing left than to hope and believe.
所以，人类除了希望和信念什么也没留下

665
01:09:01,974 --> 01:09:03,801
Blood circulation disorders.
血液循环紊乱

666
01:09:04,143 --> 01:09:06,717
Functional disorders of the higher nervous system.
较高级的神经系统机能紊乱

667
01:09:07,856 --> 01:09:09,480
Will you get him out of it?
你能治好他这些毛病吗？

668
01:09:09,649 --> 01:09:14,111
I don't know. It's not a disease, not in
the earthly sense of the word at least.
我不知道，这不是疾病，至少地球上没有这种说法

669
01:09:14,363 --> 01:09:16,570
It is...
是...
- The second stage?
- 第二阶段?

670
01:09:16,741 --> 01:09:19,825
The effect of the Dark Star's radiation.
黑色星球放射线的影响
- It means we're all in this together.
- 这就意味着我们要同舟共济

671
01:09:20,078 --> 01:09:23,993
No. Erik was exposed to direct
radiation when installing the engine.
不，埃里克安装引擎时，直接暴露在放射线下

672
01:09:24,958 --> 01:09:28,659
And where is Michael? They were both out there.
迈克尔在哪？他俩都不在

673
01:09:32,008 --> 01:09:33,716
Where's Michael?
迈克尔在哪？
- I don't know.
我不知道

674
01:09:33,843 --> 01:09:35,219
Have you seen him?
你见过他吗？

675
01:09:35,345 --> 01:09:38,631
Was Michael here?
迈克尔在这儿吗？
- No. What's the matter?
- 没有，出什么事了?

676
01:09:43,896 --> 01:09:45,391
Have you seen Michael?
你见过迈克尔吗？

677
01:09:45,940 --> 01:09:48,396
Navigation bride, find Michael!
导航控制器，寻找迈克尔!

678
01:09:51,071 --> 01:09:54,737
You aren't afraid, are you?
你们不害怕吧，是不？

679
01:09:55,827 --> 01:09:57,654
It's not that bad.
事情没有那么糟糕

680
01:09:58,621 --> 01:10:01,077
We only fell asleep.
我们只是睡着了

681
01:10:01,375 --> 01:10:05,704
But those two outside, they were fully exposed.
但那两人在外面，他们是完全暴露的

682
01:10:06,213 --> 01:10:08,883
To the radiation of the Dark Star, understand?
暴露在黑色星球的放射线之下，明白吗?

683
01:10:11,261 --> 01:10:15,591
We were protected by Ikaria's shield, we are alright.
我们被伊卡里亚的防护罩所保护，我们没事

684
01:10:17,977 --> 01:10:20,646
We are. But what about him?
我们是没事，但他呢?

685
01:10:21,063 --> 01:10:22,891
Michael is in the corridor on deck zero.
迈克尔在零甲板通道里

686
01:10:23,024 --> 01:10:25,266
What is he doing there?
他在那儿干什么？
- I'll have a look.
我去看看

687
01:10:31,409 --> 01:10:33,033
Michael!
迈克尔

688
01:10:39,418 --> 01:10:40,746
Michael.
迈克尔

689
01:10:41,462 --> 01:10:43,289
What are you doing here?
你在这儿干什么？

690
01:10:53,141 --> 01:10:56,226
Leave me alone.Leave me alone!
别管我，别管我！

691
01:10:56,812 --> 01:10:59,482
Come with us.
跟我们走
- You're sick.
- 你病了

692
01:11:04,029 --> 01:11:05,856
Leave me here.
留我在这儿

693
01:11:06,114 --> 01:11:07,525
I'm dead.
我要死了

694
01:11:07,866 --> 01:11:11,450
We will all die, but I don't want to die!
我们都将死，但我不想死!

695
